## Public Member Functions

### read() {#a4f20ee2ca37e3839b73900aef8e26ac5}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>Expected&lt; bool &gt; Reader::read (<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/msgpack/object">Object</a> &amp; Obj)</>}>
Read one object from the input buffer, advancing past it.

The <code>Obj</code> is updated with the kind of the object read, and the corresponding union member is updated.

For the collection objects (Array and Map), only the length is read, and the caller must make and additional <code>N</code> calls (in the case of Array) or <code>N&#42;2</code> calls (in the case of Map) to <code>Read</code> to retrieve the collection elements.


<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="[out] Obj">filled with next object on success.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

<SectionUser title="Returns">
true when object successfully read, false when at end of input (and so <code>Obj</code> was not updated), otherwise an error.
</SectionUser>

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/binaryformat/msgpackreader-h/#l00128">128</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/binaryformat/msgpackreader-h">MsgPackReader.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/binaryformat/msgpackreader-cpp/#l00029">29</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/binaryformat/msgpackreader-cpp">MsgPackReader.cpp</a>.
